node.text: Gina Chersevani (@mixtressdc) runs one of the coolest spots around, @BuffaloBergenDC, where you’ll find everything from fountain drinks to cocktails, all served alongside bagels, knishes, latkes, and more. Pull up a virtual seat at their bar, and if you’re in DC, be sure to swing by and check out their offerings. 📹 @buckbaymedia

node.text: @ShihoFukada filmed this beautiful video about shochu’s history and culture, how it’s made, and how to use it in cocktails—it will instantly transport you to Japan and inspire you to try shochu yourself. And to learn more about Japanese shochu, be sure to follow @jss_shochu. #shochu #shochucocktail #jss_shochu #partnerpost #imbibe #imbibegram

node.title: The story of Japanese shochu is rich and layered.

node.text: Brewing a batch of Chemex coffee every morning is one of our favorite daily rituals. The classic brewer is a cinch to use, but there are a few little tricks to getting it just right, so our friends @AllegroCoffee put together a helpful how-to. Check it out before you brew your next batch! #chemex #coffeebrewing #coffeefliicks #imbibe #imbibegram

node.text: Lately, we’ve been daydreaming about traveling to Charleston and taking a seat at #TheLivingRoom bar @TheDewberryCharleston, helmed by @prettyprettyryancasey. Join us on a virtual trip to one of our favorite cities and bars. #charlestonsc #charlestonlife #hotelbar #imbibe #imbibegram 📹 @buckbaymedia

node.text: Figuring out the right grind for your favorite brewing methods is key, so our friends @allegrocoffee put together this handy video to break it all down. #coffeefliicks #coffeeathome #coffeegrinder #imbibe #imbibegram

node.title: Have you dialed in your daily coffee grind?

node.text: Saturday project: This bright and beautiful beet/peppercorn shrub featured in Michael Dietsch’s book, Shrubs. It’s perfectly sweet and savory and delicious mixed simply with some soda water. Recipe link in our profile. 📸 @laraferroni

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Imbibe in Neon Moon Birmingham with @laurafallsdown, and @neonmoonbham. May be an image of food, drink and indoor.

node.text: An extra-fruity and decadent twist on the classic, the Strawberry Piña Colada @NeonMoonBham brings strawberry syrup and a little bit of vanilla ice cream to the mix for the ultimate summertime treat. Check out the recipe from Laura Newman (@laurafallsdown) via the link in our profile! 📸 Garrett Pinkston

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Imbibe in The Snug with @photobraggins, and @snugca. May be an image of one or more people, indoor and brick wall.

node.text: Need a good weekend soundtrack? Trevor Easter (@photobraggins) has you covered with an easy breezy playlist from @SnugCA, where music is an essential element of the bar’s fun and welcoming vibe. Check it out via the link in our profile. 📸 @anna_wick

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Imbibe in Queen's Park Birmingham with @laurafallsdown, and @queensparkbham. May be an image of drink and food.

node.text: With two types of rum and a medley of citrus and spice, Don the Beachcomber’s Nui Nui cocktail is a tropical delight, and at @QueensParkBham, Laura Newman (@laurafallsdown) stays close to the original. “I’m often surprised at how many tropical cocktails skew too alcohol-forward or overly sweet, but this one is a detectable balance of fruity, tart, and boozy,” she says. Recipe link in our profile! 📸 Marilyn Nicole Vann

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Imbibe on July 29, 2021. May be an image of indoor.

node.text: Yes, espresso machines can be expensive, and yes, there’s a learning curve involved. But if your days aren’t complete without a morning latte or an after-dinner espresso, investing in a quality, at-home espresso setup pays off in the long run. We recently tapped the equipment pros @CliveCoffee to round up some of the best tools to get you started—head to the link in our profile to check out the list.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Imbibe on July 28, 2021. May be an image of food and drink.

node.text: Saying hello to some midweek margaritas.✨☀️✨ #summerdrinks #margaritas #tequilacocktails #imbibe #imbibegram 📸 @emmajanzen

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Imbibe on July 28, 2021. May be an image of drink and indoor.

node.text: Over the past five years, there’s been an explosion of offerings in the category of alcohol-free “spirits” as bartenders and drinkers at home look for more interesting and delicious options. Head to the link in our profile to check out six bottles we recommend mixing at your next zero-proof happy hour. 📸 @newlondonlight

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Imbibe in Cafe Birdie with @cafebirdiela, and @alex_zzzzz34. May be an image of drink and indoor.

node.text: Snap peas, mint, lemon, and yuzu juice bring a fresh flavor to this aquavit-based cocktail from @CafeBirdieLA. Get the recipe from Alex Zeichner (@alex_zzzzz34) via the link in our profile. 📸 @secretstan

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Imbibe on July 27, 2021. May be an image of drink.

node.text: Just in time for ripe, juicy peaches to be making their seasonal appearance, this zero-proof mix of roasted peach and basil oleo saccharum, lemon juice, and ginger ale offers a sweet, tart, and lightly herbaceous sip of summer. Get the recipe from Laura Gajewski for @VistroPrime via the link in our profile. 📸 @laraferroni

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Imbibe in ACME Hotel Company with @hetterisbetter, @acmehotelchicago, and @theberkshireroom. May be an image of drink and food.

node.text: The Rusty Nail may be a classic winter warmer, but take it for a spin in the blender with ice and you’ve got a perfectly summery take on this Scotch cocktail. Get the recipe from Christian Hetter (@hetterisbetter) via the link in our profile! 📸 @laraferroni

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Imbibe in Gilly Brewing Co. with @thecarlymarley, and @gillybrewbar. May be an image of 1 person, food, drink and indoor.

node.text: The inspiration for @GillyBrewBar came from a desire to help change the culture of Stone Mountain, Georgia's community for future generations. As its manifesto states, Gilly is not a coffee shop; it's a reimagining of coffee culture and creativity with community at its heart. Recently, @EmmaJanzen caught up with Gilly co-founder Daniel Brown (@meetdanielbrown) to learn more about how Gilly came to be and how they’re disrupting coffee’s status quo in the best way possible. Read more via the link in our profile. 📸 @maryclairephoto

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Imbibe in Polite Provisions with @arleneibarra, @hungrybartender, and @politeprovisions. May be an image of food, drink and indoor.

node.text: Low in alcohol and undeniably refreshing, the Michelada is one of the ultimate cocktails of summer afternoons and boozy brunches. Erick Castro (@hungrybartender) adds a tropical twist to his rendition, subbing the standard tomato juice for pineapple and an extra kick of spice. Recipe link in our profile. 📸 @arleneibarra
